#LIST FUNCTION
lucky_number=["23","19","1","24","12",66"]
freinds=["rama","ramayana","krishna","vishnu"]
*append() function: If you pass another list into append(), it adds that entire list as a single nested element.
print(freinds.append("om")
#output:"rama","ramayana","krishna","vishnu","om"
*extend(): Modifies the list by appending multiple elements at once without creating nested lists.
print(freinds.extend(lucky_number)
#output:rama,ramayana,krishna,vishnu,23,19,1,24,12,66
*insert: Elements after the chosen index are shifted to the right.
print(freinds.insert(1,"om")
#output:"rama","om","ramayana","krishna","vishnu"
*Remove(): It only removes one item. If the item does not exist in the list, it throws a ValueError.
print(freinds.remove("om")
#output:"rama","ramayana","krishna","vishnu"
*clear():Removes all elements from the list, leaving it completely empty.
print(freinds.clear())
output:[]
*sort:Sorts the items of the list in-place (by default, in ascending order).
print(lucky_number.sort())
output:1,12,19,23,24,66








